{"questionId":"32384769","questionHtml":"<p>the area of the base</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong> &nbsp; (Use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></math>)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find area of one triangle using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mi>θ</mi><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>60</mn><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3923</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0M0A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></math> or equivalent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>(Use of altitude)</p>\n<p>(altitude is) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find the area of one triangle using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>×</mo><mi>h</mi></math> with their altitude.<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mn>6</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>3923</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A0M0A0</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>2</mn></math> or equivalent.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong> (Finding the area of a trapezoid)</p>\n<p>(altitude of one trapezoid is) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to find area of one trapezoid using <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfr